      "FacilityID": 32294,
      "SummaryText": "Perstorp Compounds, Inc. of 238 Nonotuck Street in Florence, Massachusetts manufactures thermoset resins.  Formaldehyde is a key component in the manufacture of these resins.  Perstorp Compounds, Inc. stores more than 15,000 pounds of formaldehyde at its Florence facility.  Therefore, the company is required to address the requirements of 40 CFR Part 68.  Perstorp Compounds, Inc. has adopted its corporate environmental, health, and safety policy, which states in essence the company will meet or exceed legal requirements, strive for continuous improvement, and take a proactive stance toward pollution prevention.  The policy can be accessed in full at the Perstorp website at www.perstorp.com.  Perstorp Compounds, Inc.'s emergency response plan is an integrated contingency plan developed using the National Response Team Guidance Document.  It is intended to comply with 40 CFR Part 68, 29 CFR 1910.38(a), 29 CFR 1910.119, and 40 CFR Part 265 Subpart D.  A company representative serves on the board of the Western Massachusetts Regional Local Emergency Planning Committee, and the company has regular contact with the Northampton Fire Department.  The Perstorp Compounds, Inc Florence site has had no accidental environmental releases in the past five years."
